6000|$|Now, here's {{something}} else I remember. It's {{about the first}} time <b>I</b> ever <b>stole</b> a watermelon. [...] "Stole" [...] is a strong word. <b>Stole?</b> <b>Stole?</b> No, <b>I</b> don't mean that. It {{was the first time}} I ever withdrew a watermelon. It was the first time I ever extracted a watermelon. That is exactly the word I want--"extracted." [...] It is definite. It is precise. It perfectly conveys my idea. Its use in dentistry connotes the delicate shade of meaning I am looking for. You know we never extract our own teeth.|$|R
